# rhcs_cluster_rosa_hcp (Resource)

OpenShift managed cluster using ROSA HCP.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/cluster_rosa_hcp/example_1.tf"}}

## FIPS usage and lifecycle

Set `fips = true` during cluster creation to request FIPS-enabled cryptographic modules for the cluster.

Lifecycle caveats:
- `fips` is immutable in this resource. Changing it after creation is rejected and requires creating a new cluster.
- Red Hat documents that FIPS must be enabled before first boot and cannot be enabled on an existing deployment. See [Support for FIPS cryptography](https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.10/html/installing/installing-fips).

